content.description:
Easy lead at the far left end of the wall. Probably the easiest route on the wall.  

  Serpents Wall, L to R 

  Slither (5.6), El Primero (5.9), God Bless the IRS (5.9), Flakey Tigress (5.7), Antivenin (5.8) , Moroccan Snake Charmer (5.8) , Sidewinder (5.10c), KB5 (5.9), Blank Page (5.11).
Tricky sequence with some hidden holds. Super fun crux with a really good heel hook!
content.protection: Bolts, sport clip anchors. You can clip the first bolt from the rock you start on without a stick clip.
content.location: Right side of Serpent Wall. Cave in at the base. Look for a notched nose up high.

content.description:
Climbs up the left face of an arete feature.  

  Good quality slab-like climbing through well placed bolts.
content.location: One route left of Sidewinder. Starts with overhang at the base. Use big block slightly to right of first bolt.

content.description: Locate MSC...and climb the rounded arete...so stay to the right of original route. Climb the orange/white rock on rounded arete. If fall off route, you will swing to the left. The climb itself is more fun than MSC. I wonder if this line could have been bolted first...just to break up the 5.8s in the area.

Same line as Moraccan Snake Charmer, however you start under the roof, hands on the right side of the horizontal crack. Crux is pulling the opening roof move. Truth be told...if your tired of doing the repetitive 5.8 grade on the wall...the do MSC variation before the original route. Or else, after pulling the roof, you'll convince yourself to not climb the rest of the route.
content.protection: 5 bolts +anchors. Stick clip to protect the crux move.
content.location: Locate roof below MSC route. Cant miss it.

content.description: Second route from the right side of the wall, on the left side of Blank Page and right side of the Moroccan Snake Charmer/Sidewinder split.

Starts in front of two trees, third route from the left on the wall. Head up to the opposite side of the slight bulge in the wall as El Primero. Crux comes when the wall goes vertical with good holds.
Route heads towards large flake near the top. Footwork is the key to this route.
content.location: Located on the dead cats annex.

content.description:
The second route on the wall starting from the left, easier climbing down low leads to a crux 2/3 up the wall moving over and around a slight bulge.  

  Serpents Wall, L to R 

  Slither (5.6), El Primero (5.9), God Bless the IRS (5.9), Flakey Tigress (5.7), Antivenin (5.8) , Moroccan Snake Charmer (5.8) , Sidewinder (5.10c), KB5 (5.9), Blank Page (5.11).

Start climb with 5.10 moves to get over the bulge at bottom. The moves are much easier above the bulge in the middle part of the route.  After clipping the second bolt, climb thru thin crux moves as the wall steepens below the anchors. A fun crux sequence requiring good foot work.

Right of Flakey Tigress, left of the two routes that go right and left around an obvious bulge at the top of the wall, heads to the anchors to the left of Moroccan Snake Charmer (left side of the bulge). Crux is getting off the ground through a low roof, then smooth sailing up to the top. There is some really poor quality rock to the left side- hang right for better rock even if it makes it a bit harder.
25' wall with a roof at the base. Semi-shady. Can sometimes be busy.
